events.name: A Talk on Flutter | GDG Nashik Launch
events.description:
Join us for our Launch Event for GDG Nashik with a quick ride to Flutter!

Here we will interact with each other and get the community running.
We will also disclose our upcoming Events and what to expect.

Key takeaways from the event are as follow:

Agenda:

Session 1:

* Introduction - 15 minutes
* What next? - 15 minutes
* Share about Google's trending products. - 10 minutes

Tea/Coffee Break - 15 minutes

Session 2:

* Quick ride to Flutter - 40 minutes

* What are your expectations from GDG Nashik? ( Discussion) - 10 minutes
* Feedback - 5 minutes
* Wrap-up. - 5 minutes

Networking time with fellow participants and GDG Nashik Team.

Link to Registration: https://goo.gl/forms/UkRmHwszAC9U90uZ2
Also, RSVP to meetup page.

See you there!

GDG Nashik Team.

events.name: Google Cloud Next '19 Extended Nashik
events.description:
Next OnAir brings together community members from around the world to be a part of the Next ’19 experience. Watch the live stream or join a Next Extended event near you.

This event will include Keynotes, QwickLabs, and Discussions from Google Next 2019.

Agenda:

10:00 - 10:15 AM - Welcome Note

10:15 - 11:00 AM - How Google Cloud does ML?
By Jayesh Bapu Ahire

11:00 - 12:00 PM - Qwik Lab 1 (Introductory ML)

12:00 -12:30 PM - Snacks

12:30 - 1:30 PM - Qwik Lab 2 (Advance ML)

Speaker Description:
Mr. Jayesh Bapu Ahire
AI, ML & Blockchain Researcher, Author and consultant.

Research Assistant at Stanford AI Lab.

Organizer of Pune Developers Community, Pune ElasticSearch Meetup group and IBM Bay Area Meetup group.

We’ll be using a tool called “Qwiklabs” as our learning platform for this Next Extended event. It will cover Machine Learning track, with these two labs:

1. Cloud ML Engine Qwik Start
2. Extract, Analyze, and Translate Text from Images

Note: Next Extended labs free of charge.

Snacks and Merchandise will be sponsored by Google. And this event will be in collaboration with PDC.

Thank you.
On Behalf of GDG Nashik

events.name: Google I/O 2019 Extended LIVE

Note: You will require an invitation to attend the event. Seats are limited, so register ASAP!

events.name: Cloud Study Jams [Beginners]: GDG Nashik
events.description:
IMPORTANT: THIS IS AN INVITE ONLY EVENT!

KINDLY CONFIRM AND REGISTER ONLY IF YOU WOULD BE ABLE TO ATTEND THE FULL DAY STUDY JAM AS PER THE TIME SPECIFIED :)

Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!

This event will include Keynotes, QwickLabs, and Discussions from Google Cloud Study Jam.

This will be Introductory hands-on lab For GCP newcomers.

Agenda:

10:00 - 10:15 AM - Welcome Note
10:15 - 11:00 AM - Introduction to Docker & Kubernetes
11:00 - 12:00 PM - Qwik Lab 1 (Kubernetes Engine)
12:00 -12:30 PM - Snacks
12:30 - 1:30 PM - Qwik Lab 2 (Managing Deployments Using Kubernetes Engine)

Speaker: Announce soon

BENEFITS:

1. Completely Free Access to paid Qwiklabs hands-on labs, for more than a month, to learn everything that you can, even apart from what we do in the lab session!

2. Earn Google Cloud badges to show your skills and expertise (which are recognized worldwide)

3. Confirmed attendees will be provided food in the afternoon.

[Mandatory] REGISTRATION LINK: https://forms.gle/J8aKa8cgkXt1Hn9S9

* Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)!
* The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers.
* For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.
* Don’t forget your charger.

Thank you.
On behalf of GDG Nashik

events.name: Flutter StudyJam

venue.name: UMS Tech Labs - Google Cloud Partner

events.description:
GDG Nashik brings for you all a different StudyJam this August.

In this StudyJam, we will be learning about how to build apps using Flutter and what great new functionalities have come along in the latest version of Flutter framework.

Our Venue Partners for this event is UMS Tech Lab.

Please note, unfortunately, RSVP on the Meetup page does not guarantee entry to the event and it is mandatory for interested participants to fill up the registration form.

Registration link :

https://forms.gle/5E8ixhFeyFvrHHRn7

Shortlisted candidates shall be notified by e-mail.

Agenda:

9:00 - 09:45 Attendee registration
09:45 - 10.00 Welcome note
10:00 - 13:00 Building apps using Flutter and Flutter Web (Hands-on)
13.00 - 13:30 Lunch
13:30 - 14:00 What Next ? Google DevFest 2019 Updates
14:00 - 14:15 Closing note

Software Downloads and Installations required -

1) Flutter - https://flutter.dev/docs/get-started/install

Requirements -

1) You should have some background on Flutter Framework.
2) Your system should ideally have 8 GB of RAM.
3) A USB cable to connect android phone to the system.
4) Android phones in case Android Virtual Device doesn't work.

*** IMPORTANT ***

* Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)!
* The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers.
* For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.
* Don’t forget your charger.

We are looking forward to meeting you soon!

Regards,
GDG Nashik team.

events.name: GDG DevFest Nashik 2019

venue.name: Nashik District Maratha Vidya Prasarak Samaj's Karmaveer Baburao Thakare College of Engineering

events.description:
Google Developer Group Nashik is proud to host its 1st edition of the Biggest Technical Event in Nashik. This will be bringing together a lot of new geeks and experienced speakers.

DevFests are community-led developer events, hosted by GDG Chapters across the globe focused on Community Building and learning about Google's technologies.

DevFest Nashik brings together the community experts in Web, Android and Cloud Technologies to Nashik for Sessions, Code Labs, etc.
Each DevFest is carefully crafted to bring together speakers from all over the world, trending topics and a lot of fun for sure.

Here are the official social media Handles of GDG Nashik to stay tuned with us:
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/GDGNashik
Meetup: https://www.meetup.com/GDG-Nashik
Twitter: https://twitter.com/GDGNashik
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/GDGNashik

IMPORTANT: THIS IS AN INVITE ONLY EVENT!

Registration details will be announced soon.

Registration is mandatory.

Note: Registering won't ensure you a seat. Our team will filter out received registration entries and will send a confirmation mail to only selected participants. Also on another important point, making RSVP here in the meetup event is not counted as a final confirmed ticket.
